oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Twisting tobacco
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group photograph of men sitting in front of a barn and twisting tobacco. The barn is located on Flynn's Lick Road in Antioch. John W. Fox is seated second from the right and and with a young boy.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Group portraits; Tobacco industry; Barns
